The USP Compact is a small frame pistol capable of firing the most powerful cartridges in 45 ACP. Based on the full-size USP models, this handy pistol combines compact size with optimum effective shooting performance. 
The USP Compact is smaller and lighter than large frame USPs and the reduction in trigger reach and grip circumference increases concealability and enhances shooting ergonomics. Unlike some subcompact pistols that use a difficult to shoot two-finger grip frame, the USP Compact uses a narrow, full-hand grip frame with a choice of interchangeable extended or flush-fitting magazine floorplates. This makes the pistol easy to shoot without sacrificing concealability. This variant of the USP Compact has a modified contoured slide and frame for effective concealability and also has a no snag, bobbed hammer. external safety and de-cocking lever.  The extended slide release is contoured to reduce wear and tear on clothing when the pistol is carried concealed.
Using a modified linkless Browning-type action, the USP Compact is built to take the punishment of high energy +P and +P+ loads. Has convenient safety/decocker and new Tritium sights.

title: For Sale:  1955 Polish Radom M44 Mosin Nagant MUST SEE, PERFECT CONDITION
location: Apex, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
I have for sale a perfect condition Polish M44 made in 1955.  I know this gun is more expensive than your bog-standard 91/30, that's because this is a collectable Mosin in perfect condition.  Polish M44s are rare, rarer still in this condition.  This was made at the Radom plant in Poland.  These were post-war rifles built for rear eschelon troops, the gun never saw service and was put away in storage.  It sat there until Poland dusted the guns off and sold them out of surplus.  The gun is totally perfect, there's no metal wear or issues with the good, it looks like it came off the assembly line yesterday.  There's no pitting or rust, no cosmoline gunked everywhere that needs to be cleaned, the trigger is far better than any Russian Mosin and the bore is perfect.  Frankly I don't think this rifle has ever been shot.  Still has it's folding bayonet that's characteristic with the M44s.  If you collect Mosins or you just want a really nice gun that shoots really cheap ammo, this thing's your ticket.  I have spam cans of ammo available to the buyer at 80$ each, I think I have about 4 cans of ammo.

NO TRADES.  PERIOD.
